Module org.nasdanika.exec
Package org.nasdanika.exec.resources

Interface Resource

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Adaptable, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, Marked, Marked, ModelElement, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Container, File
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ContainerImpl, FileImpl, ResourceImpl
    public interface Resource
extends ModelElement
    A representation of the model object 'Resource'.

    The following features are supported:

    • Name
    • Contents
    • Reconcile Action
    • Merger
    See Also:
    ResourcesPackage.getResource()

      • getContents

        org.eclipse.emf.common.util.EList<org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject> getContents()
        Returns the value of the 'Contents' containment reference list. The list contents are of type EObject. Resource contents. File contents elements are adapted to ``SupplierFactory`` and produced ``InputStream``s are contcatenated. Container contents elements are adapted to ConsumerFactory and the container is passed to their ``execute`` method.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Contents' containment reference list.
        See Also:
        ResourcesPackage.getResource_Contents()

      • getReconcileAction

        ReconcileAction getReconcileAction()
        Returns the value of the 'Reconcile Action' attribute. The default value is "Overwrite". The literals are from the enumeration ReconcileAction. Reconcile action - what to do if a resource with the same name already exists. Defalut is ``Overwrite``.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Reconcile Action' attribute.
        See Also:
        ReconcileAction, setReconcileAction(ReconcileAction), ResourcesPackage.getResource_ReconcileAction()

      • getMerger

        org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject getMerger()
        Returns the value of the 'Merger' containment reference. Merger for ``Merge`` reconcile action. Adapted to ``org.nasdanika.common.resources.Merger`` to execute actual merge.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Merger' containment reference.
